  "text": "Initially, we examine a simulated uniformly sampled signal of length , consisting of two non-harmonic chirp components, as depicted in Fig. 1 , which is corrupted by white circularly symmetric Gaussian noise with a signal to noise ratio (SNR) of 10 dB, which is here defined as [CITATION_1] where denotes the power of the signal, and the variance of the additive noise. The resulting estimates from the proposed SMUCHES method and for the reassigned spectrogram [CITATION_2] are shown in Figs. 1 and 2 , respectively. As can be seen in Fig. 2 , the reassigned spectrogram finds the two chirp components, but the estimates are blurred, as well exhibiting jumps in the frequencies. On the other hand, as can be seen in Fig. 1 , the proposed method manages to find the chirp components without any such ambiguities.",
